    "chemicalDescription": [
      "Human Embryonic Kidney Cell sr-(Rabbit Polypeptide-1 Pentapeptide-105 Rabbit Polypeptide-2 Rabbit Polypeptide-3 Pentapeptide-106 Rabbit Polypeptide-4) is a single chain recombinant peptide, produced recombinantly in human embryonic kidney cells. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the gene from sr-Rabbit Polypeptide-1, Pentapeptide-105, sr-Rabbit Polypeptide-2, sr-Rabbit Polypeptide-, Pentapeptide-106, and sr-Rabbit Polypeptide-4. The fusion peptide contains 439 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
